# ADR-0010 §5e — keep the eval metrics + training manifest committed, ignore
# the binary checkpoints. Each training cycle produces a 1.1GB merged
# safetensors + per-epoch HF Trainer state (~1.1GB × 2 epoch dirs) that
# would otherwise blow GitHub's per-file size cap and bloat clone times.
#
# What stays committed:
#   - training_manifest.json   (hyperparams + dataset shape + git_sha)
#   - eval_results.json         (baseline vs candidate metrics + delta)
#
# What is ignored:
#   - adapter/                  (raw PEFT-format model.safetensors, ~1.1GB)
#   - best/                     (intermediate sentence_transformers best dir)
#   - checkpoints/              (per-epoch HF Trainer state, ~1.1GB each)
#   - any *.safetensors / *.bin / *.pt files at any depth
#
# To rehydrate a committed run, re-run scripts/train_reranker_lora.py with
# the same training_manifest.json hyperparams + dataset run_id.

adapter/
best/
checkpoints/
*.safetensors
*.bin
*.pt
optimizer.pt
scheduler.pt
scaler.pt
rng_state.pth
